description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this simply wicked Jackson USA Custom Shop King V with Goat Skull / Pentagram graphic.

The Jackson King V is a classic Jackson design and has become an iconic guitar in the metal world. This Jackson Custom Shop masterpiece has 24 Jumbo Frets to reach the full two octaves. It features a quartersawn through-body painted maple neck, and the phenomenally fast feel of its compound-radius ebony fingerboard (12"-16") is simply breathtaking. This guitar begs to be played!

Other premium features include a single DiMarzio Tone Zone Humbucker in the bridge humbucking pickup which produces high gain heavy tones yet cleans up nicely. It is perfect for metal and rock. In addition, it has a single volume knob, Floyd Rose Original locking nut and double-locking two-point tremolo, ivoroid fingerboard and headstock binding, black hardware, black headstock with white Jackson logo, and mother of pearl shark fin inlays on it's perfect ebony neck. 

Our King V comes to us in excellent condition. There are some minor signs of player wear but no serious dings or scratches. Even the points of the V are remarkably ding free!!! The only chip or real blemish on the guitar is on one of the back beveled edges and pictured above. One of the case hinges has been damaged. All of the latches and other hinges function perfectly. 

The guitar has been freshly set up with Dunlop .10-.46 strings in standard tuning. Ships in original Jackson molded hard shell case.

title: Marshall 1974X Handwired 1 x 12" 18watt Combo Amp and Matching Marshall CX 1 x 12" Extension Cab
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this Marshall 1974X Handwired 1 x 12" 18 watt Combo Amp and matching Marshall CX extension cab. 

Our Marshall comes to us in excellent condition and sounds amazing! To really get this amp and extension cab talking you'll want to wind it up a bit! Luckily it's 18 watt output power allows for killer cranked Marshall tones at a reasonable volume level! Ships with original footswitch.

Marshall Handwired 1974X at a Glance:
  • The 1974X 1 x 12" combo amp: an authentic re-issue
  • Aged Greenback T1221 speakers
  • Original components live up to point-to-point perfection

The 1974X 1 x 12" combo amp: an authentic reissue
The 1974X is an authentic reissue of the fabled model 1974 combo of the late sixties (1966-1968). Just like the original, it boasts a point-to-point, handwired, tagboard circuit housed in an aluminum chassis, plus a valve-driven tremolo circuit. At the very heart of its simple yet effective 2-channel design can be found six valves: two ECC83s in V1 and V2, a 12AT7 in V3 (Phase Inverter) an EZ81 rectifier, and a pair of cathode biased EL84s in the power stage. As the output and mains transformers are vital components in any amplifier as they influence performance, sound, and feel, Marshall worked extremely closely with their associates at Dagnall in order to duplicate the original, off-the-shelf transformers in all areas.

Aged Greenback T1221 speakers
A contributing sonic factor in the original 1974 is the way the sound of the Celestion Greenback speaker softens with age. For the 1974X, Celestion revisited the recipe for the original Greenback T1221 speaker, and aged it. The result is a new speaker proprietary to Marshall.

Original components live up to point-to-point perfection
This new series was created to meet growing public demand and to pay homage to models that, for many players, represent the ultimate in organic, all-valve guitar tone. The primary objective was to achieve maximum authenticity in terms of components, circuitry, construction methods, materials, specifications, aesthetics, signal path, performance, tonal characteristics, and feel. All of the original components and materials were used or reproduced, and the original methods of construction employed in the late 1960s were revisited. All transformers - output and power - have been meticulously re-created by Dagnall Electronics, and each amplifier's handwired tag-board lives up to the idea of point-to-point perfection.

Marshall Handwired 1974X Features:
  • 18-watt, 16-ohm, mono 1 x 12" combo amp
  • Exclusive, aged reissue of the original 20-watt, ceramic magnet, Celestion Greenback T1221 12" speaker
  • Replica of the grey and white striped Bluesbreaker grille cloth used on the originals
  • High-grade baltic birch cabinet with finger-locked joints
Marshall CX 1 x 12" Extension Cab
This beautifully hand-soldered 20W extension cabinet pairs perfectly with the handwired 1974X combo. It features a single 12” Celestion G12M-20 Greenback speaker, specially aged to flawlessly capture that vintage 60’s vibe. With its old-school fret and classic piping, you’ll look and feel like you’re playing an original 1974 combo.

The amp and extension cab are in fantastic shape but there are some scuffs on the tolex visible in the photos above.

description:
Ibanez TSA15H 15W Tube Amplifier and Matching TSA12C 1X12 Cab made in 2010.


“The Ibanez TSA15H amplifier head combines real all-tube tone with the classic distortion and drive of a TS9 Tube Screamer pedal. A pair of 12AX7s and a pair of 6V6 power tubes drive the TSA15H, providing gentle breakup when pushed. For rich fuzz and gritty overdrive, kick on the Tube Screamer circuit. Dual operation (15-watt pentode or 5-watt triode) gives you even more flexibility, allowing you to dial in the headroom you need to play in many different environments. Matched up with a TSA112C speaker cabinet, the TSA15H has enough output to comfortably carry midsize and larger venues. If you're looking for a flexible tube amp head for a great price, then the Ibanez TSA15H is an excellent choice.”


“Looking for a classic 1 x 12" to go with your TSA15H Tube Screamer head? Check this out: the Ibanez TSA112C. The TSA112C is an 80-watt guitar speaker cabinet that comes loaded with a 12" Celestion Seventy 80 speaker. This classic speaker provides tight low end with punchy midrange and aggressive bite. If you want to get the most out of your TSA15H Tube Screamer head, then match it up with an Ibanez TSA112C cabinet.”

title: Dr. Z MAZ 38 Senior NR Head 2011
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this wicked little DR. Z

The Dr. Z Maz Sr 38 NR is an ever versatile guitar amplifier that has been gracing large stages and corner clubs for years. The 38 NR will give you plenty of clean headroom and sweet driven tones for stages of all sizes. The 38 NR features a split load cathode biased output section which yields an authority not heard in many EL84 powered amps. Compared to the reverb equipped Maz 38 you get more drive and low end thrust. The NR has a very rich dynamic gain with a tight bottom and superb clarity. It's an excellent choice for discerning rock and roots music players.

The front panel features Volume, Treble, Middle, Bass, Master, and the ever versatile Cut control. The back panel features a 4, 8, and 16 ohm speaker out. An effects loop is also standard. The 38 NR is powered by a quartet of cathode biased EL84s, has three 12AX7s in the front end, and a 5AR4 rectifier. With 38 watts at your finger tips, you can move enough air to get your guitar out in front of the band.

The Dr. Z MAZ-38 is a truly versatile amp for the working or studio musician. Whether your forte' is Blues, Country, Roots, or Rock, The MAZ 38 Senior will fit the bill.

title: Fender Custom Shop John 5 Bigsby Telecaster Autographed Guitar & Strap 2008
description:
Fender Custom Shop John 5 Signature model Telecaster in Gloss Black finish with matching headstock made in 2008. This very cool guitar features a double bound select ash body with a maple neck and rosewood fingerboard. Equipped with a Seymour Duncan “Hot-Rails” in the bridge position and a Fender Custom Shop “Twisted Tele” Single-coil in the neck position controlled by a master volume & master tone knob with a 3-way pickup selector. The all chrome hardware looks evil in the dark and blinding in the light which is perfect for any live gig! The tuning machines are Fender locking deluxe tuners which make changing strings with the factory Bigsby a breeze as well as hold excellent tuning stability. The chrome pick-guard, chrome bridge, chrome knurled knobs and chrome control plate all mold together with the dark gloss black finish with maching headstock for a work of art that shows constant reflections. The 25.5” scale length neck has a 12” fingerboard radius, a modern C shape neck profile, 22 frets and white dot inlays. The previous owner was able to have John 5 sign the guitar and the strap with a photo included of him and John 5 at a meet & greet provided. This signature perviously was personalized “To Mike” however we were able to removed this part pf the signature without damaging the original guitar finish.

This guitar is in excellent condition and is a fantastic guitar whether you are a player, a fan of John 5 or a fan of extremely cool guitars. The signature on the body was done very tastefully and was done in a spot where you can still play the guitar without constantly rubbing against it. If you do not care for the signature it is easily removable. There are minor surface scratches, and skuffs but they are very light and very difficult to see with the naked eye or photograph. The gloss black finish and mirror hardware show fingerprints and scratches very easily so while this guitar is clean now, it can become dirty and show flaws very quickly if you are not careful. This guitar also comes with a guitar strap signed by John 5, the COA and the original hardshell case with crushed red velvet interior. Freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning this guitar shreds and is ready to rock!

title: Fender Custom Shop '69 Stratocaster Relic Masterbuilt Jason Smith Floyd Rose 2009 Pink Over Black
description:
Fender Custom Shop ’69 Stratocaster Relic Masterbuilt by Jason Smith finished in pink over black with a factory aged Floyd Rose Tremolo. This is one of the most outrageous and cool Fender Masterbuilt Stratocasters we have ever come across, but of course here at Diablo Guitars we are fans of the loud and outrageous guitars of the 80’s. This 4-bolt ’69 Reissue Strat begins with an alder body, maple neck, rosewood fingerboard and the large 70’s style headstock. The finish is a pink over black relic that digs into the bare wood in certain spots and gives an overall zero f***$ given attitude. The factory Floyd Rose has been aged to the point of rusted parts (that are still fully functional and purely aesthetic) which bleeds a bit even into the white pick-guard with light rust residue (builder Jason Smith really went that far). Some other minor details that would ordinarily go unnoticed are the splashes of pink on the aged white knobs to show where the refinish would have accidentally sprayed onto the knobs.

Equipped with a Seymour Duncan SH-4 Humbucker in the bridge and Abigail Ybarra hand-wound ’69 single coils in the middle and neck positions with a 5-way switch and an S-1 switch for a large variety of coil tapping and pickup splitting capabilities. The chrome hardware consists of Fender ’69-early 70’s style components including the “F” tuning machines, an “F” 4-bolt neck plate, and the afore mentioned aged chrome Floyd Rose. The 25.5 scale length neck has a medium C shape neck profile that is a little bit beefier than most modern Strats with a very well worn finish on the back of the neck. Mother of pearl dot inlays, 21 vintage narrow frets, and a great looking and feeling rosewood fingerboard.

This guitar is in excellent condition and although it is a relic there appears to be some pick scratches that may or may not have been factory, it is hard to tell given how detailed Jason Smith got when building this masterpiece. Freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge stings and setup in standard tuning with low action and ready to shred! This guitar play absolutely fantastic! This is one of the coolest Fender Custom Shop Masterbuilts that we have ever seen and we needed to have it come through our shop! Comes with the original Fender Custom Shop late 60’s hardshell case with orange interior and COA.

title: Hughes & Kettner Duotone Tommy Thayer Signature Amp Head And Cab 2008 Germany W/COA
description:
Hughes & Kettner Tommy Thayer Signature Edition Duotone 100-watt Head And Cab. This amp is in excellent condition, and includes amp covers, original footswitch, COA Signed by Tommy Thayer, Tommy Thayer Signature edition amp poster, stickers and booklets.


The amp of choice for KISS guitarist Tommy Thayer.

KISS guitarist Tommy Thayer found his tube amp of choice in the Hughes & Kettner Duotone. In fact, he was so enthused to chance upon an amp so good that he put his name on a Duotone Signature Series model. It now adorns the amp head's shining blue Plexiglas front panel, alongside his official KISS logo.


Duotone delivers to-die-for tone, but takes the one-sound-wonder of vintage amps a significant step further. When it set out to design this modern classic guitar amp head, DuoTone collaborated with an amp-tuning specialist to embrace the pros' most frequently requested modifications. The top four demands are more tone, more attack, a tube-driven effects loop, and a clean channel that merits its name.


DuoTone went on to build the first off-the-rack amp to offer all of these special tweaks as standard features: You get supercharged classic rock tones thick enough to slice with fat, dynamic overdrive, a top-drawer clean channel, a tubedriven effects loop, and even a dual master.


Hughes & Kettner's tube amps all have distinctive personalities tailored to individual expression. Built for tube purists, each amp head, including the Tommy Thayer Signature Amp is a no-frills, straightforward original. Each packed with quality of components and an aesthetic design.


Duotone guitar amps have a no-compromise design that deliver your favorite classic rock sounds. As its name suggests, the Duotone offers two distinct tonal worlds. There's the rough-and-ready overdrive channel that packs a mighty wallop and the clean channel with dynamics galore. Plus, with the benefit of the overdrive channel's boost circuit, you have enormous gain reserves to dial in everything from a touch of grit for classic rock riffing to high gain for singing leads. The Tommy Thayer Duotone amp head delivers tube tone pure and simple”even the parallel effects loop is served by a tube. There is not a single transistor in the entire signal path.


The hallmarks of the Hughes & Kettner Duotone amps are not only its exceptional sound quality but also its reliability and stage-worthiness. All amps and amp heads from the custom tube series ship with tubes that satisfy the highest standards for quality and assure maximum reliability under even the most arduous operating conditions.

title: EVH 5150 III 6L6 3-Channel 50-Watt 2x12" Guitar Combo 2018 - 2020 Ivory
description:
EVH 5150 III 50W 6L6 2X12 Tube Combo in Ivory. Amp is Excellent Condition, however there is a ding in front of cab (see pics)


Brimming with brawny tone, the EVH® 5150III® 50W 6L6 212 Combo is arena-sized sound in a Celestion® powered compact package for more convenient transport.

Redesigned with versatile, all-new independent dual- concentric controls that allow for gain and volume level matching, this 50-watt tube combo amp boasts three channels for any playing style— crisp cleans, raw crunch or searing leads.

Delivering a full-spectrum of tone, channel one features pristine cleans, channel two kicks in with overdrive and heavy gain similar to the EVH 5150III 100S, while channel three oozes with liquid distortion. Channels one and two each have dual concentric gain/volume controls, with shared EQ (low, mid, high). Channel three has its own gain, volume and EQ (low, mid, high) controls. All three channels also have global presence, resonance and reverb controls.

Loaded with dual 12” custom special designed EVH Celestion speakers to enhance and refine both your sound and your style, this combo amp also has seven JJ ECC83 (12AX7) preamp tubes, two JJ 6L6 power tubes and front-panel adjustable power output from 50 watts down to one watt.

Other features include a single input, rear-panel selectable output impedance (4, 8 or 16 ohms) with a pair of parallel speaker outputs, rear-panel MIDI input and preamp output, rear-panel effects loop and headphone jack (mutes power amp), and a four-button footswitch that controls all three channels and reverb for easy onstage switching.

The cabinet is constructed out of birch with special internal baffling for tight and increased bass response. Wrapped in stylish Black or Ivory vinyl, the EVH 5150III 50W 6L6 212 Combo is finished off with vintage-style chicken-knobs, red LED jewel indicator, molded black plastic top handle and pop-out casters.

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this absolutely stunning Duo Jet from the Gretsch USA Custom Shop. Hand built by master luthier Stephen Stern, this beauty features a magnificent book matched claro walnut top. The body and sides are the traditional Gretsch Duo Jet mahogany but this one has not been chambered! It weighs in at an impressive 9 lbs 8.5 oz and you can hear and feel it in the remarkable TONE. Rounded out with TV Jones Power Tron pickups in both the neck and bridge, open back Gotoh Vintage Style tuners, a Tune-O-Matic style bridge with a gorgeous "V" stop tail piece, this guitar absolutely sings when plugged in. Remarkably versatile and incredibly musical. Clean, overdriven and all points in between. This amazing Masterbuilt Duo Jet does it all with ease, warmth, depth and punch. The Gretsch shallow "U" neck profile is incredibly comfortable to play and the vintage style Gretsch frets only take it one step farther.

This beautiful guitar is in MINT condition with out a single visible scratch nick or ding. It was freshly set up with D'Addario .10-.46 strings and low fast easy action. This remarkable Duo Jet from Master Builder Stephen Stern is a really special guitar. Top to bottom, front to back the Gretsch USA Custom Shop delivers the goods strait from their hands and into yours.

description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this stunning '52 Telecaster Time Machine Edition... .

Get back to the age of the original workhorse guitar with the Fender Custom Shop 1952 Time Machine Relic Telecaster in Nocaster Blonde.  It sports a hand-selected, nitro-finished ash body, a satisfying Nocaster 52 U profile neck with a modern 9.5" radius and 6105 frets, a vintage bridge with brass saddles, fat 50's Tele wiring, and Custom Shop hand wound 51 Nocaster pickups. 

With stunning vintage visuals, optimized playability, and perfectly tweaked Tele twang, this Custom Shop '52 Telecaster is the genuine article. If you like meaty necks and Tele twang, with a heavily worn look & feel, this the guitar for you. 

Our 52 Telecaster comes to us in dead mint condition. It was unsold B stock from a previous Fender dealer. The guitar has been freshly set up with .10-.46 strings in standard tuning and feels and plays every ounce as good as it looks. Ships in original Fender case and inlcudes all case candy, hang tags and COA.

title: Fender Custom Shop '59 Stratocaster Relic  Faded Ocean Turquoise 2020 w/OHSC and COA
description:
Fender Custom Shop limited 1959 Strat Relic in Faded Ocean Turquoise Finish Made in USA 2021 with OHSC. This guitar features a solid select 2-piece select alder body, a rift-sawn maple neck and flat lam rosewood fretboard. Equipped with three Fender Custom Shop Hand-Wound Texas Specials single strat pickups , controlled by a master volume with two tone controls, vintage mod wiring with tone saver treble bleed and 5-way blade switch. The 25.5” scale length neck has white micarta dot inlays and 21 jumbo frets with a 60’s oval “C” shape neck profile. The hardware is comprised of Fender six inline vintage style tuning machines, a bone nut, a 6-saddle custom shop vintage synchronized tremolo bridge and aged white top-hat knobs/accents on a 1-ply parchment pickguard.

This guitar is in “like-new” mint condition and was purchased as a B-stock from a Fender dealer., The relic and aged finish from Fender looks great! (see pics)

Guitar is freshly setup and restrung with 10-46 strings. guitar Includes original Fender deluxe hard shell case, COA and case candy (Strap, bridge cover, trem arm, hang tags, literature, tags etc)
